The paper discusses the intersection of Computational Social Choice and Parameterized Algorithmics, which involves both Artificial Intelligence and Multiagent Systems (cs.AI) and Game Theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions problems related to vulnerability of voting procedures (cs.DS) and preference aggregation in multi-agent systems (cs.SI), which are both subcategories of Theoretical Computer Science. Finally, the paper proposes research challenges related to the complexity of these problems, which could fall under the subcategory of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
